  abstract: "Beyond Observable Behavior examines how school-based behavior teams can assess and intervene when severe behavior appears to be influenced by private events, rigid internal dialogue, psychological inflexibility, or classroom context that is not captured by standard observable-behavior descriptions alone. The symposium connects latency-based functional analysis, ACT-informed behavior intervention planning, staff coaching, and outcome measurement so BCBAs can build assessment and intervention models that are technically sound, socially valid, and usable in real school settings."
